<item>
            <title>[HBASE-999] Up versions on historian and keep history of deleted regions for a while rather than delete immediately</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-999</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since removal of master logging of all rows of catalog tables, there is a hole when it comes to debugging what happened in hbase at some time in the past.  The region historian is the place we keep up region history only we&apos;ve been deleting old history when region is deleted.  Instead, lets not delete region history but keep it around a while, say a week.  Also, keep all versions &amp;#8211; currently its set to 1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To do this, may need to also so &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-998&quot; title=&quot;Narrow getClosestRowBefore by passing column family&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-998&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-998&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
